Place potatoes, onion, water, celery salt, salt, and pepper in Dutch oven and bring to boil. Reduce heat and let simmer till potatoes are fork tender. Meanwhile, mix rub noodles. Place flour in small bowl, break egg over flour, and mix with fingertips, rubbing mixture together until all flour is absorbed and small lumps form. Drop the dough mixture slowly into boiling potatoes, stirring constantly, and reduce heat. Let simmer 20 minutes, stirring frequently. Add additional salt and pepper to taste.